			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: What if the new level cap was 75?<a name="39797"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 13 04 1:06 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Bah to the original poster. Not for the AA thing, but for the silly concept that the max level will be 75.  How rediculous.
<br />

<br />
I am of the opinion that the new max level will be 68.  Yep, only 3 more levels.  
<br />

<br />
Here's why: 
<br />

<br />
- raising levels trivializes content and causes significant changes in class balance
<br />
- the more the increase, the harder it is to balance
<br />
- the more the increase, the more content becomes obsolete, requiring ever more content
<br />
- it's much easier to add a few levels with a few upgrades/spells/abilities, than it is to add lots of levels.
<br />
- adding less levels now leaves them open to adding a few levels again in the future, without obsoleting as much content
<br />

<br />
So, for the sheer, 'it's easier' argument, my money is on the idea that they will only add a few levels.  Besides, as a player, it all works out in my favor.  If I get new levels, I get new skills, AA's, abilities, stats, and new spells. Whether it's 2 levels or 5 levels really doesn't make that much difference.  It's progression that wasn't available before. 
<br />

<br />
The increase in levels will affect dps, mitigation, hps, resists, and all things that come with levels, meaning that I have additional opportunities to enjoy new content = good
<br />

<br />
Bring it on!
<br />

<br />
Wyndaria.
<br />
</span></td>
